# [cite_start]User Manual: Producer's Edge [cite: 1]

## [cite_start]1. Main Dashboard [cite: 2]

[cite_start]**PRODUCER'S EDGE: Data-Driven Decision Making** [cite: 3, 4]

The application serves as a central hub for movie producers. [cite_start]The main screen offers intuitive navigation to three core modules[cite: 8]:

* [cite_start]**Concept & Title Analysis:** Validates plot ideas and research competitor titles[cite: 9].
* [cite_start]**Talent & Casting:** Discovers high-performing actor pairs and top-grossing directors[cite: 10].
* [cite_start]**Market Trends:** Analyses genre combinations to identify profitable market opportunities[cite: 11].

---

## [cite_start]2. Module 1: Concept & Title Analysis [cite: 12]

### Functionality
[cite_start]This screen evaluates the financial potential of movie concepts (Query 1) or analyses competitor titles (Query 2)[cite: 13].

### [cite_start]Key Features [cite: 14]
* [cite_start]**Unified Search Bar:** Allows input of keywords (e.g., "Apocalypse") or specific titles[cite: 15].
* **Search Modes:**
    * [cite_start]**Search by Plot Concept:** Performs a Full-Text Search on movie overviews[cite: 23].
    * [cite_start]**Search by Title:** Finds specific films for competitor analysis[cite: 24].
* [cite_start]**Results:** As shown in the screenshot, the system displays key financial metrics including Budget, Revenue, and a calculated ROI Ratio, helping producers estimate the profitability of similar concepts[cite: 25].

### [cite_start]Data Example (from Interface) [cite: 26-48]

| ROI Ratio | Revenue | Budget | Release Year | Movie Title |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| 2.8 | $540M | $190M | 2013 | World War Z |
| 3.8 | $769M | $200M | 2009 | 2012 |
| 4.4 | $552M | $125M | 2004 | The Day After Tomorrow |

---

## [cite_start]3. Module 2: Talent & Casting Intelligence [cite: 49]

### Functionality
[cite_start]A split-screen dashboard focusing on the human capital of film production (Queries 3 & 4)[cite: 62].

### [cite_start]Key Features [cite: 63]

**1. [cite_start]Top Directors (Left Panel)** [cite: 64]
Users select the number of directors to display (e.g., Top 5). [cite_start]The system ranks them by total lifetime revenue[cite: 64, 65].

* [cite_start]Steven Spielberg - $10.5B [cite: 56]
* [cite_start]James Cameron - $8.7B [cite: 57]
* [cite_start]Russo Brothers - $6.8B [cite: 57]
* [cite_start]Peter Jackson - $6.5B [cite: 58]
* [cite_start]Christopher Nolan - $5.9B [cite: 59]

**2. [cite_start]Power Couples (Right Panel)** [cite: 66]
Users set a "Minimum Movies Together" filter. [cite_start]The system identifies actor pairs with proven on-screen chemistry and displays their average viewer rating[cite: 66, 67].

* De Niro & Joe Pesci (6 Movies) | [cite_start]8.1 Rating [cite: 60]
* Emma Stone & Ryan Gosling (3 Movies) | [cite_start]7.9 Rating [cite: 61]
* Chris Evans & R. Downey Jr. (9 Movies) | [cite_start]7.8 Rating [cite: 61]

---

## [cite_start]4. Module 3: Market Trends & Genre Analysis [cite: 68]

### Functionality
[cite_start]Identifies profitable market niches by analysing genre combinations (Query 5)[cite: 79].

### [cite_start]Key Features [cite: 80]
* [cite_start]**Revenue Filter:** A slider allows users to set a minimum revenue threshold (e.g., $500,000,000) to exclude low-budget films from the analysis[cite: 81].
* [cite_start]**Leaderboard:** The dashboard displays a ranked list of the most lucrative genre pairs[cite: 82].

### [cite_start]Data Example (from Interface) [cite: 73-78]

* **Adventure + Fantasy**
    * Average Revenue: $850,000,000 (Green Indicator)
* **Action + Sci-Fi**
    * Average Revenue: $720,000,000 (Light Green Indicator)
* **Animation + Family**
    * Average Revenue: $610,000,000 (Yellow Indicator)
